Introduced
Second Regular Session 124th General Assembly (2026)
SENATE RESOLUTION ____
MR. PRESIDENT:
I offer the following resolution and move its adoption:
1 A SENATE RESOLUTION honoring Senator Andrea
2 Hunley on her retirement.
3 Whereas, Senator Andrea Hunley has served as a member
4 of the Indiana Senate from the 46th District since 2022,
5 becoming the Assistant Minority Leader in 2024;
6 Whereas, Senator Hunley earned her bachelor's in
7 secondary education and teaching from Indiana University
8 Bloomington in 2006, a master's degree in education from
9 Indiana University-Purdue University Indianapolis in 2010,
10 and a certificate from the Prospective Principal's Academy at
11 IU Bloomington in 2011;
12 Whereas, Before serving in elected office, Senator Hunley
13 was deeply involved in education as a public school teacher,
14 working as a K-8 public school principal with Indianapolis
15 Public Schools, an assistant principal with Metropolitan School
16 District of Washington Township, and as a high school English
17 teacher with the Metropolitan School District of Wayne
18 Township;
2026 DR 3846/DI ol

2
1 Whereas, Senator Hunley is passionate about legislation
2 that has generation impact on the health and wealth of
3 individuals and communities, and she pursued that passion as
4 a member of the Senate Committees on Utilities, Commerce and
5 Technology, Education and Career Development, Pensions and
6 Labor, Tax and Fiscal Policy, Ethics, Elections, Family and
7 Children Services, and Rules and Legislative Procedure;
8 Whereas, Senator Hunley is a member of the Zeta Phi Beta
9 Sorority, Inc., and has served on several boards and
10 commissions including: All Payer Claims Database, IU
11 Indianapolis, Indiana Civic Education, Compliance Advisory
12 Panel, Doula Reimbursement, Independent Colleges of Indiana,
13 CEMETS iLab, Indiana State Museum, Medicaid Advisory
14 Committee, White River State Park, Health Care Cost
15 Oversight Task Force, Indiana Black & Minority Health,
16 Historical Sites of Indianapolis, Indiana Black Legislative
17 Caucus, Power Caucus, Trails Caucus, Rural Caucus, and
18 Small Business Caucus;
19 Whereas, Throughout her years, Senator Hunley has been
20 a great colleague and team player supporting every member of
21 the caucus with integrity and humility, earning
22 acknowledgments along the way, including: Chaplain of the
23 Indiana Black Legislative Caucus, 2023 Fellow of the Council
24 of State Governments' Bowhay Institute for Legislative
25 Leadership Development, Hoosier Women Forward Class 2
26 Alumni, Stanley K. Lacy Leadership Series from Class XLII
27 Graduate, Legislator of the Year from the Indiana School
28 Social Work Association (2025), Politician of the Year from the
29 Indianapolis Black Chamber of Commerce (2025), Public
30 Education Advocacy from the Indiana Association of
31 Superintendents of Color (2025), Community Impact Award
32 from the Phi Beta Sigma Fraternity, Inc- Xi Sigma Chapter
2026 DR 3846/DI ol

3
1 (2025), Legislative Conservation Champion from the Indiana
2 Conservation Voters (2025);
3 Whereas, Committed to the future of Indianapolis, Senator
4 Hunley has always emphasized community-driven leadership,
5 highlighting her commitment to ensure neighborhoods are
6 vibrant, safe, and thriving through immediate actions and long-
7 term visionary plans. She has consistently demonstrated
8 professionalism and leadership using her bold voice to ensure
9 quality of life for everyone in Indiana; and
10 Whereas, Senator Hunley was adopted at a young age by
11 Marvin and Karen Hill and grew up in Fort Wayne, Indiana
12 with her two siblings, and she and her husband Ryan live in
13 Indianapolis with their two daughters: Therefore,
14 Be it resolved by the Senate of the
15 General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
16 SECTION 1. That the Indiana Senate honors Senator
17 Andrea Hunley on her retirement.
18 SECTION 2. The Secretary of the Senate is hereby
19 directed to transmit two copies of this Resolution to Senator
20 Andrea Hunley.
